race.comment: ESSENTRIC NATURE (5) is looking for his fourth win in a row after storming home over 1400m last start. Back to 1200m now is a niggle, though he's drawn to sit a touch closer than he has done in recent races. Form out of his last race has been solid and he can repeat the dose. KAY TEE WHY (6) steps up to 1200m now after storming home impressively in his past couple of outings, beaten in a photo last time out as favourite. He does lose Pike, though the rise in trip looks to suit and he rates highly on recent efforts. Can get back to winning ways. SILVER EYE (7) comes through the same race as KAY TEE WHY last start and was part of that photo finish for the win. 1200m not doesn't look an issue and while he has drawn wide, he can storm home over the top. CESSATION (10) hits this third-up and is not to be discounted down in the weights. TOO DARDY (9) beat home a number of these last start and has to be included.
